                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Hearings on bills to furnish emergency food relief assistance to India were begun
                    by the House Committee on Foreign Affairs on February 20, 1951, with testimony
                    by Secretary Acheson and officials from various parts of the government. See <hi
                        rend="italic">India Emergency Assistance Act of 1951; Hearings Before the
                        Committee on Foreign Affairs, House of Representative, Eighty-Second
                        Congress, First Session … February 20, 21, 22, 23, 1951</hi> (Washington,
                    Government Printing Office, 1951). Secretary Acheson’s testimony is also printed
                    in the Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 12, 1951, page
                    424.</p>
                <p>For additional documentation on House consideration of aid to India, see <hi
                        rend="italic">House Report No. 185 … on H.R. 3017</hi> (March 5, 1951) and
                        <hi rend="italic">Staff Memorandum: Additional Information on H.R. 3017,
                        India Emergency Assistance Act of 1951</hi> (March 6, 1951) (Washington,
                    Government Printing Office, 1951).</p>
            </div>
